caption:
WHEN: Thursday, September 5th, from 5 - 8 PM 

WHERE: OI2296 (OISE) 

Looking to test your transit knowledge? Or to just make some new friends on campus? Join us for fun games, a team-based Kahoot and snacks at UofT Rocket Riders' first ever game night event! This event is open to everyone, including those who have not signed up as a member. 

*Register now through the link in our bio!

🚀🚇 SPECIAL OFFER 🚇🚀
Want to join the Rocket Riders? Now you can do so for just $5! The membership form is in our link in bio. Membership fees can be paid via e-transfer, or by cash at the clubs fair.
Join us today and become part of the first transit-oriented student club at U of T St. George!

📣 The deadline for applications to become a Robonars Associate has been extended! 📣

Apply by August 10th, 2024 @ 11:59 PM EST.

Become a Robonars Associate and showcase your skills in event organization and communication, and take advantage of a great opportunity to network with relevant faculties and organizations.

Apply now to contribute to the next generation of robotics leaders through seminar-style events.

🔗 Application link in bio!

🚨🚨THERE IS ONE DAY LEFT TO SUBMIT YOUR PROJECT PROPOSALS‼️ As a team lead, you will have the opportunity to form and lead your own project team, collaborate with developers, and present your project at various UTMIST showcase events throughout the year!

📨 Application link, project proposal guide & role description slides ➡️ Our Bio‼️

📆 Due: Applications due 16th August at 11:59PM EST and will be reviewed on a rolling basis! 

📌Current Opportunities:
✔️Engineering Team Lead
✔️ML Software Research Lead
✔️AI Open-Source Lead

‼️ Applications will close on 16th August at 11:59 PM and we will be reviewing them on a rolling basis so apply fast! For those who applied you will receive an email from us shortly regarding the interview time. We can’t wait to see your applications and welcome you to our team! 🙌 

Any questions can be sent to us directly on the general channel on UTMIST’s Discord server or e-mail at utmist@studentorg.utoronto.ca!
